.TH SHOTPLAN "8" "juillet 2026" "Shotplan 1.0.0" "System Administration Utilities"
.SH NAME
Shotplan \- Test plan execution tool providing screenshots and videos reporting
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shotplan
\fI\,OPTIONS \/\fR[ \fI\,<SHOTPLAN PATH> \/\fR[ \fI\,<PLAN NAME> \/\fR[ \fI\,ANY \/\fR] ] ]
.PP
Arguments:
.IP
<plan file path>
.IP
The shotplan file where the tests are defined (YAML format)
.IP
[<plan name>]
.IP
Optional: the name of the test (shot) plan to execute (instead of all).
.IP
[<any string>]
.IP
Optional: the providing of any third argument indicates only to run the last step of the specified shot plan.
.PP
OPTIONS:
.PP
\fB\-\-cat\fR
.IP
List available categories
.PP
\fB\-\-debug\fR
.IP
Activates debug logs
.PP
\fB\-\-force\-defaults\fR
.IP
Forces default values for required user input to be used and
do not ask user to enter a value
.PP
\fB\-\-from\fR =STRING
.IP
The test plan from which to start the test execution
.PP
\fB\-C\fR =STRING
.IP
Test category to run
.PP
\fB\-F\fR, \fB\-\-filelist\fR
.IP
Prints the list of output files (images and videos) as they
would have been generated during plan execution.
.PP
\fB\-M\fR, \fB\-\-manpage\fR
.IP
Generates command samples for manpages based on the shot
plan
.PP
\fB\-P\fR, \fB\-\-planids\fR
.IP
Prints the logical Ids of all defined test plans.
.PP
\fB\-R\fR, \fB\-\-report\fR
.IP
Switch on generation of run reports
.PP
\fB\-T\fR, \fB\-\-no\-report\fR
.IP
Switch off generation of run reports (default)
.PP
\fB\-a\fR
.IP
Switch off interactivity
.PP
\fB\-i\fR
.IP
Switch on interactivity (default)
.PP
\fB\-y\fR
.IP
Assume 'Yes' when prompted for confirmation
.SH DESCRIPTION
shotplan is a test execution and reporting tool which enables to define and execute tests launched and controlled by script.
.PP
The tests to run and the control scripts are defined in a YAML configuration file where the sequence of tests are defined and programmed in script. The YAML file is also called test plan or shot plan, and is by convention named .
.PP
A test plan splits into a sequence of test cases (also called test plans), in which a sequence of test steps are defined.
.PP
shotplan reports about each executed test and its result on the standard output, including a dated test banners indicating version and revision control numbers of tested items, test tools and dependencies.
.PP
Shotplan takes its name by the fact that the tool is capable of producing screenshots and video captures for executed tests.
.SH EXAMPLES
Testing with reporting (screenshots)
.IP
\f(CW$ shotplan --report\fR
.PP
Testing without reporting
.IP
\f(CW$ shotplan --T\fR
.PP
Testing starting from a certain plan, use option \-\-from, e.g
.IP
\f(CW$ shotplan --from-init\fR
.PP
To test release version inside a docker
.IP
# ON HOST: this starts container and release package are auto installed
.IP
\f(CW$ shotplan --C\fR
.IP
# INSIDE CONTAINER execute actual shot plan , interactive
.IP
\f(CW$ test_arcv --force-defaults -C all -y -T -i\fR
.IP
# INSIDE CONTAINER execute actual shot plan in automatic mode
.IP
\f(CW$ test_arcv --force-defaults -C all -y -T -a\fR
